(162, 2, 'sankey/applying', 'Draft description...', 'sankey/applying', 1, 2, '<h1>Applying This Data</h1> <p><strong>The "What Paths Do They Follow?" page is intended to provide a clearer picture of the relative rates of migration into and out of the selected major as well as where they go or from where they came.</strong></p> <p>This chart is based only on the students&apos; major as declared at entry and at graduation. It does not show intervening discipline changes for students who made multiple migrations during their academic career. This chart also does not include students who are still enrolled, who transferred out of the university, or who did not graduate.</p> <p>This data may be of interest in its own right, but is likely most useful as a point of consideration when interpreting other data in this report or from other sources. For example, if, when reviewing the data in the &ldquo;Who Are My Students?&rdquo; page, you see that there are fewer juniors and seniors in the selected major than you expected, you might explore this chart to see if transferring to other majors is a contributing factor.</p> <p>Here are a few suggestions for applying this data:</p> <ul> <li>For majors that predominantly attract many students from other majors, consider reviewing where those students originate and discuss with other faculty and departments how well prepared they may be for the selected major when they arrive.</li> <li>For majors that predominantly send many students to other majors, consider surveying and discussing with departing students their reasons for changing majors.</li> </ul>', 'chris', '2016-09-20 22:42:15', '2016-09-20 22:42:15', NULL),
